cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

The paper presents a novel deep reinforcement learning-based resource allocation technique for a cognitive radio network, which involves both machine learning and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with multi-agent environments and coordination, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
